40class RTCPReceiver;

43class RTCPSender final {
44 public:
45 struct FeedbackState {
46 FeedbackState();
47 FeedbackState(const FeedbackState&);
48 FeedbackState(FeedbackState&&);
49
50 ~FeedbackState();
51
52 uint32_t packets_sent;
53 size_t media_bytes_sent;
54 uint32_t send_bitrate;
55
56 uint32_t last_rr_ntp_secs;
57 uint32_t last_rr_ntp_frac;
58 uint32_t remote_sr;
59
60 std::vector<rtcp::ReceiveTimeInfo> last_xr_rtis;
61
62 // Used when generating TMMBR.
63 RTCPReceiver* receiver;
64 };
65
66 explicit RTCPSender(const RtpRtcpInterface::Configuration& config);
67
68 RTCPSender() = delete;
69 RTCPSender(const RTCPSender&) = delete;
70 RTCPSender& operator=(const RTCPSender&) = delete;
71
72 virtual ~RTCPSender();
73
74 RtcpMode Status() const RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(mutex_rtcp_sender_);
75 void SetRTCPStatus(RtcpMode method) RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(mutex_rtcp_sender_);
76
77 bool Sending() const RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(mutex_rtcp_sender_);
78 void SetSendingStatus(const FeedbackState& feedback_state,
79 bool enabled)
80 RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(mutex_rtcp_sender_); // combine the functions
81
82 int32_t SetNackStatus(bool enable) RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(mutex_rtcp_sender_);
83
84 void SetTimestampOffset(uint32_t timestamp_offset)
85 RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(mutex_rtcp_sender_);
86
87 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/6458): Remove default parameter value when all the
88 // depending projects are updated to correctly set payload type.
89 void SetLastRtpTime(uint32_t rtp_timestamp,
90 int64_t capture_time_ms,
91 int8_t payload_type = -1)
92 RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(mutex_rtcp_sender_);
93
94 void SetRtpClockRate(int8_t payload_type, int rtp_clock_rate_hz)
95 RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(mutex_rtcp_sender_);
96
97 uint32_t SSRC() const { return ssrc_; }
98
99 void SetRemoteSSRC(uint32_t ssrc) RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(mutex_rtcp_sender_);
100
101 int32_t SetCNAME(const char* cName) RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(mutex_rtcp_sender_);
102
103 bool TimeToSendRTCPReport(bool sendKeyframeBeforeRTP = false) const
104 RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(mutex_rtcp_sender_);
105
106 int32_t SendRTCP(const FeedbackState& feedback_state,
107 RTCPPacketType packetType,
108 int32_t nackSize = 0,
109 const uint16_t* nackList = 0)
110 RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(mutex_rtcp_sender_);
111
112 int32_t SendLossNotification(const FeedbackState& feedback_state,
113 uint16_t last_decoded_seq_num,
114 uint16_t last_received_seq_num,
115 bool decodability_flag,
116 bool buffering_allowed)
117 RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(mutex_rtcp_sender_);
118
119 void SetRemb(int64_t bitrate_bps, std::vector<uint32_t> ssrcs)
120 RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(mutex_rtcp_sender_);
121
122 void UnsetRemb() RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(mutex_rtcp_sender_);
123
124 bool TMMBR() const RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(mutex_rtcp_sender_);
125
126 void SetMaxRtpPacketSize(size_t max_packet_size)
127 RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(mutex_rtcp_sender_);
128
129 void SetTmmbn(std::vector<rtcp::TmmbItem> bounding_set)
130 RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(mutex_rtcp_sender_);
131
132 void SetCsrcs(const std::vector<uint32_t>& csrcs)
133 RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(mutex_rtcp_sender_);
134
135 void SetTargetBitrate(unsigned int target_bitrate)
136 RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(mutex_rtcp_sender_);
137 void SetVideoBitrateAllocation(const VideoBitrateAllocation& bitrate)
138 RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(mutex_rtcp_sender_);
139 void SendCombinedRtcpPacket(
140 std::vector<std::unique_ptr<rtcp::RtcpPacket>> rtcp_packets)
141 RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(mutex_rtcp_sender_);
142
143 private:
144 class RtcpContext;
145 class PacketSender;
146
147 absl::optional<int32_t> ComputeCompoundRTCPPacket(
148 const FeedbackState& feedback_state,
149 RTCPPacketType packet_type,
150 int32_t nack_size,
151 const uint16_t* nack_list,
152 PacketSender& sender) RTC_EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(mutex_rtcp_sender_);
153
154 // Determine which RTCP messages should be sent and setup flags.
155 void PrepareReport(const FeedbackState& feedback_state)
156 RTC_EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(mutex_rtcp_sender_);
157
158 std::vector<rtcp::ReportBlock> CreateReportBlocks(
159 const FeedbackState& feedback_state)
160 RTC_EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(mutex_rtcp_sender_);
161
162 void BuildSR(const RtcpContext& context, PacketSender& sender)
163 RTC_EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(mutex_rtcp_sender_);
164 void BuildRR(const RtcpContext& context, PacketSender& sender)
165 RTC_EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(mutex_rtcp_sender_);
166 void BuildSDES(const RtcpContext& context, PacketSender& sender)
167 RTC_EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(mutex_rtcp_sender_);
168 void BuildPLI(const RtcpContext& context, PacketSender& sender)
169 RTC_EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(mutex_rtcp_sender_);
170 void BuildREMB(const RtcpContext& context, PacketSender& sender)
171 RTC_EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(mutex_rtcp_sender_);
172 void BuildTMMBR(const RtcpContext& context, PacketSender& sender)
173 RTC_EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(mutex_rtcp_sender_);

175 RTC_EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(mutex_rtcp_sender_);
176 void BuildAPP(const RtcpContext& context, PacketSender& sender)
177 RTC_EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(mutex_rtcp_sender_);
178 void BuildLossNotification(const RtcpContext& context, PacketSender& sender)
179 RTC_EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(mutex_rtcp_sender_);
180 void BuildExtendedReports(const RtcpContext& context, PacketSender& sender)
181 RTC_EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(mutex_rtcp_sender_);
182 void BuildBYE(const RtcpContext& context, PacketSender& sender)
183 RTC_EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(mutex_rtcp_sender_);
184 void BuildFIR(const RtcpContext& context, PacketSender& sender)
185 RTC_EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(mutex_rtcp_sender_);
186 void BuildNACK(const RtcpContext& context, PacketSender& sender)
187 RTC_EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(mutex_rtcp_sender_);

189 const bool audio_;
190 const uint32_t ssrc_;
191 Clock* const clock_;

212 ReceiveStatisticsProvider* receive_statistics_

215 // send CSRCs
216 std::vector<uint32_t> csrcs_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(mutex_rtcp_sender_);
217
218 // Full intra request

221 rtcp::LossNotification loss_notification_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(mutex_rtcp_sender_);

223 // REMB

225 std::vector<uint32_t> remb_ssrcs_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(mutex_rtcp_sender_);
226
227 std::vector<rtcp::TmmbItem> tmmbn_to_send_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(mutex_rtcp_sender_);
228 uint32_t tmmbr_send_bps_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(mutex_rtcp_sender_);
229 uint32_t packet_oh_send_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(mutex_rtcp_sender_);

233 const bool xr_send_receiver_reference_time_enabled_;

235 RtcpPacketTypeCounterObserver* const packet_type_counter_observer_;

238 RtcpNackStats nack_stats_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(mutex_rtcp_sender_);
239
240 VideoBitrateAllocation video_bitrate_allocation_
241 RTC_GUARDED_BY(mutex_rtcp_sender_);
242 bool send_video_bitrate_allocation_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(mutex_rtcp_sender_);
243
244 std::map<int8_t, int> rtp_clock_rates_khz_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(mutex_rtcp_sender_);
245 int8_t last_payload_type_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(mutex_rtcp_sender_);
246
247 absl::optional<VideoBitrateAllocation> CheckAndUpdateLayerStructure(
248 const VideoBitrateAllocation& bitrate) const
249 RTC_EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(mutex_rtcp_sender_);
250
251 void SetFlag(uint32_t type, bool is_volatile)
252 RTC_EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(mutex_rtcp_sender_);
253 bool IsFlagPresent(uint32_t type) const
254 RTC_EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(mutex_rtcp_sender_);
255 bool ConsumeFlag(uint32_t type, bool forced = false)
256 RTC_EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(mutex_rtcp_sender_);
257 bool AllVolatileFlagsConsumed() const
258 RTC_EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(mutex_rtcp_sender_);
259 struct ReportFlag {
260 ReportFlag(uint32_t type, bool is_volatile)
261 : type(type), is_volatile(is_volatile) {}
262 bool operator<(const ReportFlag& flag) const { return type < flag.type; }
263 bool operator==(const ReportFlag& flag) const { return type == flag.type; }
264 const uint32_t type;
265 const bool is_volatile;
266 };
267
268 std::set<ReportFlag> report_flags_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(mutex_rtcp_sender_);
269
270 typedef void (RTCPSender::*BuilderFunc)(const RtcpContext&, PacketSender&);
271 // Map from RTCPPacketType to builder.
272 std::map<uint32_t, BuilderFunc> builders_;
273};
